### Description

I am trying to write unit test for my component but I am unable to change my input value  inside `afterNextRender`

    
```ts
constructor() {
  afterNextRender({
    write: () => {
      if (this.disabled()) {
         this.myStream.next('hello');
      }
    }
  });
}
```

```ts
it('should emits value to the stream when disabled is true', async () => {
  fixture.componentRef.setInput('disabled', true);

  await firstValueFrom(component.myStream);
      
  expect(component.disabled()).toEqual(true);
});
```

The test waits forever then fails. it seems that `afterNextRender` is executed in the constructor as soon as the component is created in the unit test, the input is false at that time, I need to be able to set the input first then call it to execute, similar to how we do with `ngOnInit` for instance.

It is not mentioned in the docs, how to unit test the rendering life cycles.

How can I do this test with `afterNextRender`?

